main event: A pilot spotted an unidentified white, round, basketball-shaped object maneuvering erratically above Duluth, Minnesota on April 2, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 30 minutes, oscillating in elevation and azimuth.
The Air Force was unable to determine the exact nature of the object, but believed it could have been a balloon reflecting sunlight.
Two F-89 fighter jets attempted to reach the altitude of the object but were unable to do so.
Weather stations in St. Cloud and Minneapolis reported balloon releases during the same time period.
The pilots stated that the object looked similar to a balloon.
